BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:task-uzel-auth-20260325@predictor_ingest
DTSTAMP:20260325T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260325
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260326
SUMMARY:Implement Cloudflare Access login for UZEL hub preview
DESCRIPTION:Implement Cloudflare Access as the auth gate for UZEL hub preview access.\n\nInfrastructure context:\n- Domain: Porkbun registered\n- DNS/proxy: Cloudflare (proxied — Hetzner IP not exposed)\n- Web server: Caddy on Hetzner (handles TLS via Cloudflare)\n- AI agents platform: Nginx now → Caddy eventually\n- New repo: uzelhub-dash-web (site-wide content)\n\nApproach: Cloudflare Zero Trust Access (already in stack — 5 min setup)\n  Browser → CF Access login wall → CF proxy → Caddy → web/\n  No Caddy config changes. No code changes. Hetzner IP stays hidden.\n  Free tier: up to 50 users. Supports Google / GitHub / email OTP.\n\nSteps:\n  1. Cloudflare dashboard → Zero Trust → Access → Applications\n  2. Add Application → Self-hosted → set subdomain (e.g. preview.uzelhub.com)\n  3. Set policy: allow by email list or Google Workspace domain\n  4. Enable "App Launcher" if multi-domain access needed\n  5. Test with incognito window\n\nDecisions needed:\n  - Which subdomain? (preview.uzelhub.com vs graph.uzelhub.com)\n  - Auth method: Google SSO or email OTP?\n  - Per-domain access policies or single global policy?\n  - uzelhub-dash-web: will it share the same Access application or separate?
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
